    Title: 'registration: duare sarkar focus on migrant workers',
    Article:
      "kolkata: the state government is gearing up for the seventh edition of its flagship outreach programme 'duare sarkar'. the camps are scheduled to start on friday. they will continue to function till september 16. the special focus this time will be on registration of migrant labourers, along with old-age pension.to make it a success, 41 senior ias officers have been entrusted with the responsibility of districts and subdivisions for intense monitoring.citizens can submit their applications for 35 types of services. in the second part -- from september 18 to 30 -- there will be outreach camps for service delivery. the new services in this edition are registration of migrant workers , enlistment of artisans and weavers and registration on the udhyam portal.for registration with the west bengal migrant workers welfare board, the migrant workers can register even through their family members if they are now out of bengal, said khursheed ali qadri, dm of west midnapore. however, the application needs to be accompanied by a self-declaration along with a photograph, an aadhaar card copy and bank details. the newly formed welfare board aims to resolve problems faced by the migrant workers while working outside bengal. it will provide various aids, which includes compensation in case of death or disability and ferrying them home in case of any disaster.duare sarkar, launched in 2020, has already delivered services to 7.2 crore people through 4.6 lakh camps. in this edition, around a lakh camps are being planned at the booth levels. for people living in remote areas, there will be mobile camps, said chief secretary hk dwivedi.",
