    Link: 'https://news.google.?hl=en-IN&gl=IN&ceid=IN%3Aen',
    Title:
      '3 booked for spreading fake news on migrant workers being attacked in tamil nadu',
    Article:
      'tamil nadu police registered a case against three in connection with the fake news that circulated on social media regarding migrant labourers being attacked in the state.\nagainst the backdrop of a video that went viral on social media where migrant labourers from bihar were brutally thrashed, bihar cm nitish kumar took to twitter and showed his concern over the safety of the migrants.\nadvertisement\nhours later, tamil nadu police claimed that the video that was circulating on social media regarding labourers from bihar being killed was fake.\nalso read | \'fake news,\' says tn dgp after bihar cm expresses concern over migrant labourers killed in tamil nadu\nthe editor of dainik bhaskar was charged under indian penal code sections 153 (a) and 505 (i) (b). the case was registered in thirumuruganpoondi police station.\ncyber crime unit of thiruppur police registered a case against mohammed tanveer who owns tanveer post under sections 153 (b), 505 (ii) (b) of ipc and 56 (d) of the information technology act.\nthe thuthukudi police also registered a case under sections 153, 153 a, 504, 505(1) (b), 505 (1) (c) and 505(2) against prashant umrao and have created special teams to arrest them.\nreacting to this unrest in the state, chief minister mk stalin said, "those who spread rumours claiming that other state\'s migrant workers are being attacked in tamil nadu, are anti-nationals."\n"stern legal action will be taken against those who attempt to spread false information using videos of crime that has occurred in other states," the tamil nadu cm added.\nalso read | false information is being spread: officials on fake news over attack on bihari migrant workers in tamil nadu\ntamil nadu police has also issued a clarification that migrant north indian workers are living safe without any fear. details are being gathered about those who are trying to spread false information and caused unrest in the stated.\nthe police further added that strict action would be taken against the culprits.\ntamil nadu bjp president k annamalai said that migrant workers are safe and secured in tamil nadu and that there was a deliberate attempt to malign the state\'s reputation through false news.',
    Summary:
      'The editor of dainik bhaskar was charged under indian penal code sections 153 (a) and 505 (i) of the information technology act. The case was registered in thirumuruganpoondi police station. The police said that the video that was circulating on social media regarding migrant labourers being killed was fake. The police also said that migrant workers are safe and secured in tamil nadu. The state has also issued a clarification that migrant. workers are living safe without any fear. The government has created special teams to arrest the culprits and that the police will be taking action against the culprit\'s. "stern legal action will be taken against those who are attempting to spread false information," the police said.',
