      'koraput: a nabarangpur police team on wednesday rescued 16 migrant labourers, including three minors, from a prawn processing unit in andhra pradesh , where they were reportedly tortured.police said that lured by a middleman, identified as premananda muduli , at least five persons of deopali village under khatiguda police station in nabarangpur and 11 from kalahandi district travelled to machilipatnam in krishna district of andhra pradesh in march."the agent had promised a monthly salary of rs 10,000 to each labourer along with free food and accommodation. however, they were not paid and were tortured by the employer," said s sushree , nabarangpur sp.police said one of the workers managed to contact his relative over the phone and narrated their plight. accordingly, a case was registered in khatiguda police station. a special police team reached machilipatnam and rescued the labourers. "the agent is on the run and efforts are on to apprehend him," the sp said.',
